COVID-19 Community Helpline

Organization: Student-led Initiative
Duration: Second Wave of COVID-19, India (2021)

During the second wave of the COVID-19 pandemic in India, I co-founded and managed COVID.UOH, a student-led initiative that 
provided real-time information on the availability of oxygen cylinders, hospital beds, blood plasma, medical supplies, and 
other emergency resources. Working alongside more than 30 student volunteers across Telangana and Andhra Pradesh, we 
established a coordinated helpline that verified and disseminated critical information to individuals and families seeking 
urgent medical assistance.

Through continuous coordination, volunteer management, and information verification, the initiative helped connect people 
with life-saving resources during one of India's most challenging public health crises.

